Male genitalia (
Fig. 12
). Uncus broad at base, narrowed to pointed apex, with long setae laterally. Gnathos almost as long as uncus, broad, sub-rectangular, widened apically, with scale-like protuberances distally, obtusely rounded apically. Valva with basal 3/5 wide, subparallel, distal 2/5 narrowed to apex; costa slightly concave basally and distally, convex medially, with a densely setose, overlapped triangular area distally. Sacculus with basal 3/5 wide, distal 2/5 slightly narrowed to apex, curved by a right angle preapically and then produced to pointed apex, with long setae medially. Saccus about 3/5 length of valva, wide at base, narrowed distally. Juxta narrowly connected at base, straight on anterior margin; lateral arm straight, triangularly produced distally, reaching posterior 2/3 of tegumen. Aedeagus almost 2.5 times as long as valva, broad at base, narrowed to basal 1/3, uniformly slender for distal 2/3; with two small spine-like cornuti almost equal in length, one straight, another slightly curved.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 15
). Apophyses anteriores about half length of apophyses posteriores. Lamella postvaginalis large, inverted triangular. Ductus bursae extremely long, basal 1/3‒1/2 membranous, remaining part sclero- tized, distal half coiled, gradually expanded to entrance of corpus bursae. Corpus bursae rounded; signa small, elliptical, edged with denticles.
